##8-year-old daughter with rare disease takes two weeks to save her life

Micro Signal NDDAILY

Feature presentation, Nandu, in a different way

Today is Rare Disease Day. Even in people who are not newly diagnosed with pneumonia, the epidemic continues to affect families with rare diseases.

Tuberous sclerosis, an 8 year old girl from rural Hubei Province with a rare disease, now has enough medicine in her home to last only two weeks.

Tuberous sclerosis, patients face to the nose as the center to both sides of the nose wing to grow nodes in the shape of butterflies, hence the name "bow tie disease. ".

At the moment of the epidemic, road closures, traffic inconvenience, cheap medicine can not buy, expensive medicine can not afford. All of which makes it difficult to stay on your medication. If there is no medicine, happy will fall into a state of persistent epilepsy, breathing difficulties, rescue in time will be life-threatening.

[ NANDU N video ] video: Nandu special correspondent, Dong Zihao, Su Hailun, later: Chen Jiehao Editor: Chen Beilei

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Southern Metropolis Daily recently received a call from a happy mother, Yu Yuan, who said she was running out of medicine for her child. She used to buy medicine from Daigou, which comes back from Turkey, but she hasn't been able to buy it recently, "The drugs have been on edge since last November. ".

Beijing's Tuberous Sclerosis Center for rare diseases told Nandu that the life-saving drug for patients with Tuberous Sclerosis, also known as Xibaoning, has neither been manufactured nor sold in China, families of rare patients can only buy drugs on behalf of someone else, "and the movie I am not a drug God is similar to the plot. ".

More than 300 patients with rare diseases are currently facing drug shortages, according to the Kord Rare Disease Center (CORD) in Nandu. Although there are also xibaoning sold in Hong Kong, but the Hong Kong version of Xibaoning Poryǒng 见 Boryeong more expensive, the epidemic also affected the shipment, "light appeal is not effective, hope that more people see the difficulties of patients' families. "

Life-saving drugs are expensive and hard to buy

On Feb. 21, Nandu reporters arrived at their happy home in the town of Zhakou in Gong'an County after driving dozens of kilometers from downtown Jingzhou, Hubei Province, through checkpoints and multiple temperature checks.

Happy, tall,. Just after her eighth birthday, she was nearly five feet tall. Adults say that when she grows up, she will have a "clothes rack figure" . Born in Shenzhen in 2012, Tuberous sclerosis was diagnosed at 11 months of age. "Diagnosis: Tuberous Sclerosis, intractable epilepsy, congenital heart disease, autism, " read a medical certificate issued by the Shenzhen Children's Hospital.

8-year-old happy life can not take care of themselves, do not know how to express, can not communicate with people, need 24-hour care. When she had the seizure, the seizure was like a demon haunting her.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Happy Mother Yu Yuan, 40, is a single mother. Forced by the pressures of life, she returned to her rural hometown of Jingzhou, Hubei Province, last year, happy to have worked as a fast food restaurant worker in Shenzhen.

In the happy room, I kite will take the children's Daily medicine lined up. "Xibaoning, debaking, Sirolimus, all of them. Mainly Xibaoning, for infantile spasms, " Yu said, "If you can buy Turkey's Keppel, the price should be 500 yuan a box by now. " Keppel also has a Hong Kong version, which is not easy to get, with prices ranging from 1,200 yuan to 1,500 yuan, too much for the happy family.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Happy Medicine can last two weeks, Yu Kite is very worried.

NANDU reporters learned that the original research drug xibaoning production side is a French company. Cord staff say they may be able to try to help with the purchase of the Hong Kong version, "we can link all the resources and all the parties involved to address the needs of patients. ".

The son of Liu Jinzhu, director of the Tuberous sclerosis in Beijing, is also a Tuberous sclerosis patient. He told Nandu that since there was no manufacturer in the country to produce xibaoning and no formal channels to sell the drug, the patients' families had to buy the drug through the agency, "walking on the edge of the law, similar to the plot of the movie "I am not a drug God. ".

Liu Jinzhu said that fortunately there was no shortage of debakin and Sirolimus in the country, "Sirolimus and north China Pharmaceutical co-operation, before a specific number of production. "

At least 300 patients with a rare disease like this are out of medication

It is normal to be hard to find urgently needed drugs for rare diseases. Some people also call them orphan drugs. Rare disease patients less, less market demand, high R & D costs, enterprise input-output inequality factors such as the long-term existence of this situation. Cord workers say they recently counted more than 300 Tuberous sclerosis patients who are facing drug shortages, adding to the urgency of the new crown pneumonia outbreak.

Liu Jinzhu told the NANDU reporter, for patients in Hubei Province, the problem of drug shortage is quite serious, because of the epidemic, the purchase of drugs, drug delivery is very inconvenient. Cord staff said that despite the closure of Hubei Province, the CORD  is working with wuhan-related logistics agencies, volunteer teams and online drug sales platform to solve the last hurdle for patients seeking medicine.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
February 21st is a happy birthday. In the past, her family bought her a delicious birthday cake, this year because of the epidemic, the village closed, the cake can not be bought. On This Day, her family prepared her favorite instant noodles, a simple birthday.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Happy like pig Petch and Super Flash, want to play mobile phone, know how to ask your mother. She hugs her peers warmly, but doesn't talk much, leaving them confused and scared, so she doesn't have many children to play with. She loves small animals that can grab a goose by the neck and never let go. She was clean, didn't like to play in the fields, and never used the bathroom when she was a guest.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Happy GRANDPA outside to do odd jobs, "repair the road" , in order to take care of happy, he went home. Grandma and GRANDPA have four or five acres of land, grow some soybean cotton, raise some fish, to make a living. After returning home, my mother Yu Yuan, to do self-employed sister to work, "day to her there to help, try to come back early in the evening to accompany happy. ".

"She chose me, and I did my best. "

According to the Tuberous sclerosis, one in every 6,000 new born babies in the world, one in every 20 minutes on earth, and about 100,000 in China's Tuberous sclerosis, there are more than a million Tuberous sclerosis worldwide.

On May 11,2018, the Tuberous sclerosis and other five departments jointly developed the first rare diseases catalogue, which was included. Liu said this meant that the state recognized the disease and "hoped that the regulators would tilt the scales in their policy-making. "

Happy Pretty rely on her mother, although not normal speech, but through the way to touch her head to express love to her mother. 'Now that I'm back home, my only thought is to take good care of my daughter, ' Ms. Yu said. "I used to go to the hospital every three months, and have an MRI of my head and abdomen every six months. I didn't go to the hospital for the last two years. I planned to take her for a full checkup during the Spring Festival, and I couldn't get out even if the epidemic came. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"The child will cost 3,000 to 4,000 yuan a month, " Yu said. "As long as the medication is guaranteed, I can accept her even if she is in a bad condition. Since she chose me, I will try my best to take care of her. "

Recalling her daughter's road to recovery in Shenzhen, Yu said that those years had been very difficult, although every day was very hard, but did not feel tired.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
She will always remember happy 10 months ago, "when she was lively and lovely, she seemed to understand everything I said. "

(the name Yu Yuan is a pseudonym)
